			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Hardboard, also known as high-density fibreboard (HDF), is an engineered wood product made from compressed wood fibres. It is created by breaking down wood into fibres, then combining them with a bonding agent and applying high pressure to form a dense and durable board. It is not milled directly from trees like a 2×4 is. The wood has been broken down, processed, mixed with a variety of substances, and then re-formed into solid boards. Hardboard has high density and high strength, which is a quality substitute for wood and is the commonly-used panel in building decoration and for furniture manufacturing.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硬纸板又称高密度纤维板（HDF），是一种由压缩木纤维制成的工程木制品。它是通过将木材分解成纤维，然后与粘合剂结合，再施加高压形成致密耐用的板材。它不像 2×4 木板那样直接从树上碾磨而成。木材经过分解、加工、与各种物质混合，然后重新形成实心板。硬纸板密度大、强度高，是木材的优质替代品，是建筑装修和家具制造中常用的板材。</common:generalComment>
